name: Rush Limbaugh
summary: Rush Hudson Limbaugh III was born on January 12, 1951, in Cape Girardeau, Missouri, and died on February 17, 2021. He was a conservative American radio talk show host, political commentator, and author, best known for The Rush Limbaugh Show, which aired nationally from 1988 to 2021. Limbaugh became a polarizing but influential figure in American media, shaping conservative discourse and earning accolades like the Presidential Medal of Freedom in 2020. His career spanned over five decades, marked by both widespread popularity and significant controversy over his rhetoric and views.
